Just now realized how good of an allegory it really is

For example we hate a certain girl because we find her cruel, but learn she lost her father and it caused her great grief she was unable to recover from. Our scorn was built on ignorance so knowledge made love possible. Omniscience and God's infinite love go hand in hand I think.

One small window into God's mind from our own experience in life is that generally the more we know about someone, the more we tend to find loving him or her easier. Even a vile person can turn lovable to us if we know details from his childhood, his moments of weakness, etc.
